      "description": "Available is a mechanically sorted 2002 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine. This unit maintains exceptional volumetric efficiency with its individual throttle bodies and a recently overhauled double VANOS system. Power is managed via a Getrag 420G six-speed manual transmission, delivering torque to a factory M-Variable locking differential. Critically, the rear subframe has been reinforced with plates, and the rod bearings have been replaced as preventative maintenance. The suspension retains its original geometry but benefits from upgraded polyurethane bushings for improved lateral stability. While the aesthetics reflect a well-enjoyed driver's car, the powertrain remains tight with linear power delivery up to the 8,000 RPM redline. A technically sound specimen for the enthusiast who prioritizes chassis dynamics and mechanical integrity.",
